We have recommended that the Management, thru the Local Chief Executive: 

Direct all the accountable officers, who are in custody of unserviceable properties, to return the same to the GSO-Designate for the institution of measures for the proper disposal of these properties in accordance with Title V of COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books the unserviceable and missing or non-existing properties upon the completion of the disposal procedures as required in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 and Title V of COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992;

Instruct the GSO-Designate to institute measures for the proper disposition of non-existing /missing properties in accordance with Items 7 & 8 of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to take up the necessary accounting entries to recognize in the books of accounts the loss of PPE and, where appropriate, to set up the corresponding receivables from concerned accountable officers/ personnel for the non-existing/ missing PPEs;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the adjusting entries for the reclassification of PPE items below the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00 to appropriate accounts;

Instruct the GSO-Designate to cancel the Property Acknowledgement Receipts of the properties below the capitalization threshold and issue an Inventory Custodian Slip in lieu thereof; and

Require the Inventory Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances of the Municipality.

